\int\dfrac{x-1}{\sqrt{x}+1}\,\mathrm dx
\begin{align} \int\frac{x-1}{\sqrt x+1}\,\mathrm dx &= \int (x-1)(x^{1/2}+1)^{-1}\,\mathrm dx \\ &= \frac23 x\sqrt x+\frac12x^2 - 2x^{1/2}-x+c \end{align}
\frac{x-1}{\sqrt{x}+1}=\sqrt{x}-1.
\frac{y^2-1}{y+1}=\frac{(y-1)(y+1)}{y+1}=y-1
y=\sqrt{x}
\int \frac{x-1}{\sqrt x+1}dx=\int (\sqrt x-1)dx
\int x^m\ dx=\frac{x^{m+1}}{m+1}+C
m\ne-1
